A slotted rest variable used in <Atom>s, <Expr>s and <Plex>s. See...
an extension point for specializations of the slotted rest tag name. Stripe-skipping is not
an extension point for specializations of the slot tag name.
In atomic formulas, zero or more slots are allowed.
Slotted rest arguments follow the ordinary slots in atomic formulas in the normal-form serialization.
Slotted arguments follow positional arguments in
atomic formulas in the normal-form serialization.
